node.text:
This year's @metmuseum @metcostumeinstitute exhibit will focus on fashion, as told through the lens of gender, race, and equity and I'm thrilled Instagram is part of it. I've gotten a sneak peek at the stunning curation that Andrew Bolton is pulling together... it's going to be a memorable one. See you in September... #MetInAmerica
🎥 @happymonday

node.text: Got the incredible life opportunity to chat (virtually, alas) with @barackobama about his new book A Promised Land and he gave me advice on how to write my own (long-delayed, sorry @caithoyt) book. Please watch to the end to see Ren and Tao's cameo and my (I think rather crafty) mom skills at wrangling them. For the record, I called President Obama a T.Rex, not a giraffe.

node.text: No exaggeration: This is probably the best photo I’ve ever taken. Tom and River swaddled and sleeping at the hospital last week… looks like Tom is in the bassinet too 😂😂. Big thank you to all the nurses and PAs and staff @nyphospital who were so wonderful and my OB Robert Sassoon and Stephanie/Cindy at his office!! I feel like I just gave an Oscars acceptance speech but honestly isn’t having a baby just as hard as making a movie 😬

node.text: Welcome to the world, baby River! You are only a day old but mom is already doing photo dumps of you. Sorry about that 🤷🏻‍♀️. We named you after grandpa (yie yie) on dad’s side… between Ren, Tao, and Juno all the grandparents are covered 🥰. We love you immensely and can’t wait to introduce you to the world… and for you to teach us as well. ❤️❤️❤️
